According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Dairy Cultures Market was valued at USD 1.25 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 1.32 billion in 2026 to USD 1.89 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 6.9% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion as consumers increasingly seek probiotic-rich dairy products, clean-label food ingredients, and functional nutrition. Rising demand for fermented dairy products such as yogurt, cheese, kefir, buttermilk, and cultured beverages, coupled with continuous innovation in microbial strain development, is driving significant opportunities for dairy culture manufacturers worldwide.
